⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Julia
node 1984 · 1984 · ⟦Julia:1984:d42024⟧

WHO   — Julia — rebellion through the body
WHAT  — Winston's lover and his opposite kind of rebel: she fights the Party not with ideas but with appetite and private joy.
WHERE — 1984 · 1984  Framework inputs: Nineteen Eighty-Four (George Orwell, 1949)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because resistance is not only the mind's; Julia rebels through the body the Party tries to ration and shame.
HOW   — By cunning, sex, and a practical refusal to let the Party own her private wants — though she, too, is broken.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I rebelled with my body, not my mind — and in the end they made us betray each other, which was the only victory they wanted.

